RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': 'Based on the trace analysis tool results, I can clearly identify the root cause from the available data. The trace analysis shows a consistent pattern of "connection refused" errors when services attempt to connect to the CartService at IP address 10.233.46.196:7070.\n\nThe key findings from the trace analysis are:\n\n1. **Connection Refused Errors**: Multiple services (frontend pods and checkoutservice) are failing with "connection error: desc = \\"transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 10.233.46.196:7070: connect: connection refused\\""\n\n2. **High Error Volume**: \n   - frontend-1: 870 occurrences of GetCart failures\n   - frontend-2: 672 occurrences of GetCart failures  \n   - frontend-0: 658 occurrences of GetCart failures\n   - Total HTTP 500 errors: 2570+ across all frontend pods\n\n3. **Missing Server Spans**: The fact that I cannot retrieve any cartservice or redis-cart server spans (due to trace directory issues) combined with the "connection refused" errors strongly indicates that the cartservice is completely down/unavailable.\n\n4. **Fast Fail Pattern**: The errors show "connection refused" rather than timeouts, which indicates the service is not accepting connections at all - this is a fast fail scenario suggesting the cartservice pod has crashed or is not running.\n\nThe root cause is clearly the **cartservice** being unavailable, which causes all dependent services (frontend and checkoutservice) to fail when trying to access cart functionality. The redis-cart dependency is not the issue here since the connection is failing at the cartservice level before it would even reach redis.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_trace_keys": ["error_ratio", "frontend->cartservice", "connection_refused", "checkoutservice->cartservice"],\n  "affected_components": ["cartservice"],\n  "missing_traces": ["cartservice server spans", "redis-cart server spans"],\n  "trace_summary": "Frontend and checkoutservice calls to cartservice fail with \'connection refused\' errors (2570+ HTTP 500 errors). The connection refused pattern indicates cartservice is completely down/unavailable, causing cascading failures. No server spans available for cartservice suggests the service crashed.",\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_pod_status_at_timestamp",\n    "reason": "Connection refused errors indicate cartservice pod likely crashed or is not running",\n    "suggested_metrics": ["pod_processes", "pod_restart_count"],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["cartservice", "OOMKilled", "exit", "crash"],\n    "critical_timestamp": "2025-06-05 18:10:05"\n  }\n}\n```'}
